-- Philadelphia Eagles Fire Andy Reid as Coach After 14 Seasons
-- B y   A a r o n   K u r i l o f f
-- 2012-12-31T15:07:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-31/philadelphia-eagles-fire-andy-reid-as-coach-after-14-seasons.html
Andy Reid  was fired today after 14
seasons as coach of the Philadelphia Eagles, the longest active
tenure in the National Football League.  The Eagles reached the playoffs nine times under Reid but
finished 4-12 this season, capped by a 42-7 loss to the New York
Giants yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  